  "excerpt": "A new installation at this year’s Festival des Architectures Vives in Montpellier draws attention to food waste through an unexpected medium: stale bread. Titled Paysage de Pain (Landscape of Bread), by MERO Studios, the project uses hundreds of recovered baguettes to form a walkable...",
